Two Ethiopian nationals were on Friday slapped with a 30-day jail term for being in the country illegally. The two brothers Daniel Tamirat and Daniel Tamire appeared before a Magistrate court in Kwale County. Principal Magistrate Patrick Wambugu the two had pleaded guilty to being in the country unlawfully contrary to Kenyan citizenship and immigration act. The duo was arrested at Goshani village in Vigurungani location in Kinango sub-county on February 28, 2020. They, however, asked for court mercy but the Magistrate said the two should be deported back home immediately they finish their sentence. The court also advised them to seek asylum if they want to stay in Kenya but their motive must first be known. They are serving their sentences at GK prison in Matuga constituency.